Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.32,0:00:03.52,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I've liked you, Chisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.89,0:00:05.02,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,For quite a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:47.08,Episode-Title,title,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Eleven: \NThe Changing Times
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.58,0:01:50.02,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Um, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.74,0:01:53.60,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.60,0:01:55.81,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:02:00.80,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for causing a stir \Nso early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.22,0:02:03.97,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I just confessed my \Nfeelings to your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.14,0:02:06.45,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.45,0:02:07.94,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,How polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:11.73,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I want a reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.34,0:02:15.23,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,It's sort of like a modest resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.23,0:02:16.93,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Resistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.14,0:02:18.26,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.26,0:02:19.81,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hurry, \Nwe're going to be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.81,0:02:21.49,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.59,0:02:36.08,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.08,0:02:37.32,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,You're really far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.32,0:02:39.44,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.44,0:02:41.77,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Then good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.37,0:02:47.77,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Looking back at it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.03,0:02:53.55,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I think that Kaname and Chisaki \Nwere a little weird that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.35,0:02:56.64,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.64,0:03:00.61,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,my thoughts were full from the \Nupcoming cold, the Ofunehiki,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.98,0:03:04.12,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,and Manaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.82,0:03:07.62,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And I think Manaka was the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.53,0:03:15.38,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Manaka and I could have \Nnever caught on to those two at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.58,0:03:11.59,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:13.02,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:14.12,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.13,0:03:15.38,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.95,0:03:19.88,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,The fact was that, in the\Nfew days that followed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.88,0:03:24.63,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,the world that surrounded us \Nchanged at an unbelievable pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.80,0:03:27.65,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.65,0:03:29.64,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,the saltflake snow continued to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:34.85,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,When we realized it, our village \Nhad turned completely white,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.07,0:03:37.40,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,like somewhere from the snow country.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.62,0:03:44.53,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Along with that, the preparations \Nfor our sleep were continuing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:42.03,Closed,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Closed to Prepare for the Sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.56,0:03:51.44,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone stopped eating,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.80,0:03:55.70,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,and their Ena just kept getting thicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.08,0:04:03.57,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,At first, "the moment" just felt like something \Nvague, but eventually it was right in front of our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.95,0:04:08.03,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,There was no way to think of it \Nas some kind of joke anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.26,0:04:13.48,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,On the surface, the saltflake \Nsnow had only fallen once more,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:16.56,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,but because of the overly chilly summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:20.73,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I think everyone started to \Nwork a little more seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:23.87,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.13,0:04:28.88,Main,village	A,0000,0000,0000,,According to Uroko-sama, with how \Neveryone's Ena is coming along,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.88,0:04:32.12,Main,village	A,0000,0000,0000,,we should probably fall \Ninto our sleep on the 21st.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:33.60,Main,village B,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:34.75,Young Men's Coalition,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Young Men's Coalition
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:34.75,Main,village B,0000,0000,0000,,The 21st?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.75,0:04:36.80,Main,village B,0000,0000,0000,,That's the day of the Ofunehiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.96,0:04:39.31,Main,village C,0000,0000,0000,,So on the day of the festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.31,0:04:42.42,Main,village C,0000,0000,0000,,we'll be cheerfully saying goodbye \Nto everyone on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.85,0:04:47.74,Main,village B,0000,0000,0000,,All of them will just have to \Ncool their heads off in the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:50.74,Main,village B,0000,0000,0000,,Those ungrateful, shameless jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.06,0:04:55.94,Main,village C,0000,0000,0000,,Though actually, right now we're\Nthe ones with the thicker skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:57.56,Main,village A,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:59.19,Young Men's Coalition,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Young Men's Coalition
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.19,0:05:00.37,Main,village C,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.37,0:05:06.49,Main,village C,0000,0000,0000,,The guys on the surface right now might \Nnot be there anymore when we wake up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.95,0:05:11.83,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.09,0:05:15.79,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:15.79,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:21.63,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.63,0:05:23.34,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Have a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.52,0:05:27.84,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.84,0:05:30.20,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,There hasn't been much change.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.20,0:05:33.47,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,It might be because I've been \Nout of the sea for so long,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.47,0:05:36.10,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,but it appears that it's \Naffecting me a lot less.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.54,0:05:40.56,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,But I probably shouldn't \Ntry to diet for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.10,0:05:46.32,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Here. I filled it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.57,Marriage Registration,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Marriage Registration
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.57,husband,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Husband-to-be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.57,wife,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Wife-to-be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.57,Name,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Name
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.57,(Reading),sign,0000,0000,0000,,(Phonetics)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.57,Sakishima Akari,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Sakishima Akari
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.89,0:05:55.08,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,You sure it's okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.28,0:06:08.34,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I may be inexperienced, \Nbut please stay with me for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:15.35,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,S-Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.20,0:06:22.08,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and about the ceremony...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:23.48,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.72,0:06:26.79,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking we probably \Ndon't need to bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.79,0:06:28.20,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Considering the times,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:31.16,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure my dad won't \Ncome even if I invite him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.77,0:06:34.84,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.83,0:06:38.25,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,don't you think that's exactly why \Nwe should have a proper ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.25,0:06:43.40,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure your dad would like \Nto see you as a bride as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.28,0:06:46.71,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,So let's think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.10,0:06:50.47,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,There should be a ceremony \Nthat is suitable for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.91,0:06:53.87,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,and I still don't want to give up on\Ngetting your dad's blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.87,0:06:55.72,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,on our relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:01.63,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Itaru-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.68,0:07:06.98,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,This country originally had\Na temperate humid climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.41,0:07:11.11,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,The biggest characteristic of that\Nis the changes in the seasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.57,0:07:15.54,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,and the thing affecting this \Nis called the seasonal winds...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.80,0:07:18.83,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.83,0:07:20.48,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.48,0:07:21.46,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:24.24,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,It's still before noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.56,0:07:27.34,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Our Ena is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.34,0:07:30.92,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,But these are instructions from Shioshishio.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.92,0:07:33.17,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should follow them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:38.26,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Your hibernation is thought \Nto be a biochemical reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.26,0:07:40.69,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,to special environmental factors adding up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:45.75,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,But this hasn't happened these past \Nfew centuries, so we're not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.96,0:07:48.45,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But Sensei, we're fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:51.73,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.97,0:07:57.62,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:07:59.00,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.29,0:08:03.13,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Your Ena's become thicker, and \Nit needs water more often.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:05.13,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.94,0:08:34.28,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.28,0:08:36.51,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,It's already dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.51,0:08:39.09,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We seriously are going to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.37,0:08:40.55,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.59,0:08:46.70,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking, even if people \Nsleep at the same time at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.70,0:08:49.20,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,everyone still wakes up \Nat various times, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:53.55,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So are we all really going to be \Nable to wake up at the same time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.93,0:08:59.47,Flashback,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't everyone going to sleep \Ntogether and waking up together?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.53,0:09:04.43,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,There's no guarantee.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.09,0:09:10.89,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,After our hibernation, not only will the \Nsurface be different, but so will we.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.82,0:09:16.82,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,The only guarantee we have of spending the same time together is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.65,0:09:20.08,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,It's sort of ephemeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.32,0:09:26.08,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,What did you guys want \Nto do about lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:29.21,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei asked me to ask \Nyou guys just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.44,0:09:36.05,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,You really do have \Namazing timing, Tsumugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.38,0:09:41.01,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.76,0:09:44.40,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You'll get in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.40,0:09:45.52,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Like I care!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.13,0:09:48.11,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not just going to fall sleep helplessly,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.11,0:09:51.02,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,when I don't even know \Nwhat's going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:01.75,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Manaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.13,0:10:10.33,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.52,0:10:14.36,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to eat, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.36,0:10:18.05,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I mean... I don't want it to be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:24.64,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to go to sleep and have \Neverything be different when I wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.20,0:10:28.52,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Manaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.78,0:10:53.21,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.80,0:10:54.98,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.26,0:11:02.34,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Hii-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.66,0:11:08.45,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Manaka really is a fast runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.86,0:11:11.05,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,She's usually really slow,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.05,0:11:12.98,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,but sometimes we get left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.61,0:11:17.32,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hurry, Egawa and the \Nothers are going to eat it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.30,0:11:20.18,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.18,0:11:20.99,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.11,0:11:24.99,Saya_Mart_Ep_11,,0000,0000,0000,,Saya Mart
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.55,0:11:27.57,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,I really understand now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.57,0:11:31.87,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,how much the people from \NShioshishio helped out our store.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:33.64,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Due to bad weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.64,0:11:36.39,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,the produce and fish have all \Nbeen stuck at a steep price.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.88,0:11:39.78,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the world really \Ncould be ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.78,0:11:41.88,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do our best, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:45.26,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,This is the time to put \Ngood things on sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.94,0:11:54.49,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,You saw, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.49,0:11:55.88,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.62,0:11:59.12,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.12,0:12:01.71,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Go away somewhere, Aka-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.58,0:12:06.37,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,I said go, you fake mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.70,0:12:07.99,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Miuna!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.05,0:12:12.12,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,That made Aka-chan mad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.12,0:12:14.78,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,This will make her go \Nback to the sea, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.78,0:12:16.40,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,She'll go to sleep, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.40,0:12:17.85,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,She won't die, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.85,0:12:19.38,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cry, Miuna!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.38,0:12:21.47,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,We're red demons that cried!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:23.01,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't have a choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.57,0:12:28.96,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:32.93,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,But where I'm headed has \Nalready been decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.14,0:12:35.22,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Sakishima-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.28,0:12:37.29,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.74,0:12:40.61,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,We're from the Fishery \NCooperative's Young Men's Coalition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:44.24,Main,guy b,0000,0000,0000,,We had a request for your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.82,0:12:46.08,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,For Hikari?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:54.66,Main,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.08,0:12:57.05,Main,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.05,0:12:58.10,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:01.09,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any way that \Nyou'd do the Ofunehiki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.09,0:13:03.07,Main,guy b,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.07,0:13:04.69,Main,old b,0000,0000,0000,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.41,0:13:08.34,Main,old b,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about what happened \Nat our last meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.34,0:13:09.31,Main,old b,0000,0000,0000,,We, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.31,0:13:11.47,Main,old b,0000,0000,0000,,let our tempers get the best of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.47,0:13:14.27,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.65,0:13:16.66,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, are you being serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.66,0:13:17.65,Main,guy b,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.94,0:13:21.08,Main,guy b,0000,0000,0000,,When you first told \Nus about the winter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.29,0:13:24.15,Main,guy b,0000,0000,0000,,we weren't really sure what to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.15,0:13:27.39,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the saltflake snow falling \Nand the weather being what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.39,0:13:29.98,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,everyone realized it might be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.98,0:13:31.79,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,So please!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.79,0:13:33.04,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,We beg of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.70,0:13:38.20,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:42.22,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,These people were laughing \Nat what you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.22,0:13:45.47,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,but now that the fishing's not good \Nand they see what's happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.47,0:13:47.88,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,they want to be on board with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:53.39,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,You have every right to decline considering \Nhow convenient this sounds for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.74,0:13:58.18,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,But, if possible, please \Naccept their plea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.50,0:14:01.56,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,The surface is a very \Nimportant place to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.52,0:14:09.16,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.65,0:14:15.00,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So everyone on the surface is \Ngoing to help us out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:17.97,Main,guy b,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we'll help\Nin any way we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.40,0:14:21.59,Main,guy b,0000,0000,0000,,This is the consensus opinion of \Nthe Oshiooshi Fishery Cooperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.59,0:14:23.22,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.22,0:14:24.75,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Then leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:27.86,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.86,0:14:31.66,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone from the Fishery Cooperative \Nsaid they'd help with the Ofunehiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.66,0:14:34.46,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.46,0:14:36.50,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Very well done, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.81,0:14:41.98,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,However, even if you go through with \Nthe Ofunehiki, nothing will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.98,0:14:43.11,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.73,0:14:46.03,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.60,0:14:48.19,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.19,0:14:51.97,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? I was just asking
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.97,0:14:55.24,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,if you could move the \Nmen on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:58.75,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Did I ever say that would \Nresult in anything further?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.24,0:15:04.56,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.56,0:15:06.71,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Save the surface!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:09.72,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you! Save them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.89,0:15:15.55,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,I am but the scale of the Sea God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.55,0:15:19.07,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,My powers will not extend beyond the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.07,0:15:21.56,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing I can \Ndo about the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:24.23,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:34.95,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Uroko-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:37.85,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,You knew all this yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.85,0:15:41.19,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that the Ofunehiki \Nhad no meaning or power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.04,0:15:44.33,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.71,0:15:48.34,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the humans \Nweren't a total loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.71,0:15:52.81,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to say to them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.05,0:15:55.55,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,After all of them worked so hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.25,0:15:58.75,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And they're still working hard as we speak...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.75,0:16:00.31,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:04.98,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I know that all those guys would never \Nhave wanted to bow their heads
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:06.49,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,to a kid like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.09,0:16:08.69,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But they did anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.09,0:16:13.04,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And I said that I'd do it and \Nthat they could leave it to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:15.66,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,You did your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.66,0:16:18.97,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. Everyone knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.12,0:16:21.38,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.86,0:16:23.54,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.16,0:16:26.90,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,There was something I \Nwas thinking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.69,0:16:38.13,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I brought them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.02,0:16:44.40,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.40,0:16:46.14,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a violation of human rights!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.14,0:16:48.04,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll sue!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.94,0:16:48.52,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.36,0:16:51.82,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:54.78,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you all for gathering here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:57.93,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I had something I wanted \Nto ask of all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.57,0:17:00.73,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I think that you are all aware by now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.73,0:17:06.00,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,but Shiodome Itaru-san and \NI are going to be married.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.96,0:17:08.06,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.06,0:17:11.28,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering if it would be possible
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.28,0:17:13.67,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,to do the Ofunehiki \Nand wedding together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.38,0:17:16.60,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Together?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.59,0:17:20.62,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering if you'd let \Nme take Ojoshi-sama's place
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.62,0:17:22.85,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,on the boat to be sent out to sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.85,0:17:24.74,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,But does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.74,0:17:26.81,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to be the sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.81,0:17:29.48,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,and try to calm the Sea God's rage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.29,0:17:35.32,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,But Uroko-sama said there was \Nno point in the Ofunehiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.18,0:17:37.57,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.57,0:17:41.64,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,If Uroko-sama said that, I'm \Nsure nothing will happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.64,0:17:44.54,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,and there may be no \Npoint in me doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.88,0:17:48.50,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,But if there's nothing \Nelse that we can do,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.74,0:17:51.68,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I want to try everything \Nwe can just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.31,0:17:55.34,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be the Ojoshi-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.76,0:17:57.70,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,And when the Ofunehiki is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.70,0:18:02.64,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I will marry Itaru-san as if I \Nwere going to marry the Sea God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.76,0:18:06.39,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Will you... forgive me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.72,0:18:09.04,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.04,0:18:11.12,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Because if you go to sleep in the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.12,0:18:13.40,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be able to keep living, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.40,0:18:17.37,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Then I want you to \Nkeep living, Aka-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.87,0:18:23.41,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,But I need you and \NItaru-san in my life now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.50,0:18:28.43,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in me living \Nif I don't have you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.43,0:18:32.63,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,So, I'm sorry, but I definitely
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.63,0:18:34.43,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,won't go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.80,0:18:38.68,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to live my life in the same \Nplace and time as you, Miuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.62,0:18:41.23,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Aka-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:47.49,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.66,0:18:58.07,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if it's futile.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:01.38,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought I needed \Nto do something, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.38,0:19:04.12,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,after seeing all of you work so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:07.70,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Because I don't want to \Nsay goodbye to all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:12.76,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,without trying anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.77,0:19:25.01,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.06,0:19:32.18,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's a great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.18,0:19:34.44,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.73,0:19:37.90,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,want to do this together!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:39.62,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,The wedding!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.18,0:19:41.07,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.07,0:19:42.47,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:46.03,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,It would suck if this just ended \Nwith us being swallowed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:47.37,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.32,0:19:52.26,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch, Sea God!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.26,0:19:56.79,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We'll put on such a flashy ceremony, \Nthere'll be no way you can ignore it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.79,0:19:58.42,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.44,0:20:06.00,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And so, the Ofunehiki \Nwas put in motion again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.68,0:20:14.45,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the very first one our \Nancestors put on for the Sea God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.31,0:20:19.78,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,With the assistance of the \NFishery Cooperative,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.29,0:20:23.69,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,the fishermen started \Nhelping us out as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:28.04,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to use the shipyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.75,0:20:33.04,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,so it wasn't just us anymore, \Nbut the adults were helping out, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.53,0:21:01.33,Main,old,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.45,0:21:01.72,Main,old,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.72,0:21:02.99,Main,aki,0000,0000,0000,,See you tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.99,0:21:05.20,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.78,0:21:10.11,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Akari-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.11,0:21:12.71,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Could you check the fire and the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.17,0:21:23.42,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,It's so amazing. It's very admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.42,0:21:26.55,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,No... not just Akari-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.55,0:21:31.49,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,But Hikari, and Manaka, are \Nboth trying hard to change,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.49,0:21:35.31,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,and have changed, and started \Nchanging everyone around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.04,0:21:38.81,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,It's sort of like a modest resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.46,0:21:41.67,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Kaname, too, probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.16,0:21:44.32,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Akari-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.54,0:21:47.32,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to confess \Nmy feelings to Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.84,0:21:50.14,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,It might not do any good,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.14,0:21:55.20,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't let it end without \Ntrying or without changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.22,0:21:59.07,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Because that's what I believe, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.93,0:23:32.80,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I love Manaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.80,0:23:34.85,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand any of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.85,0:23:36.40,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,This is the best that I can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.40,0:23:37.10,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.10,0:23:38.14,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:40.10,Episode-Title,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Twelve:\NI Want to Be Kind
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:40.69,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We won't... see each other anymore...
